com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.se

Class InetAddress

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.ausregistry.jtoolkit2.se.InetAddress
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Appendable, java.io.Serializable

    public class InetAddress
extends java.lang.Object
implements Appendable
    Host Internet addresses are configured and viewed via instances of this class. InetAddress instances may be supplied to the HostCreateCommand and HostUpdateCommand (indirectly via HostAddRem) constructors in order to assign or remove Internet addresses to and from host objects. They are also used to view Internet address information retrieved from a HostInfoResponse instance.
    See Also:
